  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The hemolysis sub-model employs the power-law cumulative damage integral (Giersiepen-Wurzinger formulation), which is theoretically valid under the assumption that red blood cell (RBC) damage accumulates linearly and independently across successive sub-threshold stress exposures — an assumption established for quasi-steady, low-turbulence shear environments. Validation activities were conducted at the nominal design operating point (3.5 L/min, 2400 RPM); the broader COU spans five flow-speed combinations that include off-design regimes where unsteady recirculation and elevated turbulent normal stresses may render the linear damage superposition assumption questionable.",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
